and you know it.

285
00:30:26,232 --> 00:30:28,792
- For God's sakes, let this thing go!
- I can't.

286
00:30:28,792 --> 00:30:30,672
- You think this is your big story.
- My parents are from Mexico.

287
00:30:30,672 --> 00:30:35,072
- You identify with it.
- I'm one of them. Can't you see?

288
00:30:38,552 --> 00:30:41,872
My parents came here
as migrant farm workers.

289
00:30:43,912 --> 00:30:45,632
They were killed...

290
00:30:47,632 --> 00:30:49,152
so I was adopted.

291
00:30:56,192 --> 00:30:59,752
I only have vague
memories of them.

292
00:31:01,952 --> 00:31:06,472
I remember a field
filled with workers...

293
00:31:09,152 --> 00:31:10,552
My mother.

294
00:31:12,032 --> 00:31:13,512
My father.

295
00:31:18,592 --> 00:31:20,632
I was there when he was killed.

296
00:31:26,072 --> 00:31:27,952
I saw him die.

297
00:31:29,912 --> 00:31:33,712
- I'm sorry.
- When I met Eva, I saw myself.

298
00:31:33,712 --> 00:31:39,512
I've been running away
from who I am my whole life.

299
00:31:41,592 --> 00:31:44,752
Because you don't wanna be Mexican,
not in this country.

300
00:31:47,712 --> 00:31:49,112
You see?

301
00:31:54,192 --> 00:31:56,912
I could be one of the women
in those factories.

302
00:32:00,792 --> 00:32:03,192
It could be me
in one of those graves.

303
00:32:09,192 --> 00:32:11,112
I can't let this go.

304
00:32:44,312 --> 00:32:47,192
Alfonso, hurry.
What are you doing?

305
00:32:47,192 --> 00:32:49,512
Just a minute, my love.

306
00:33:13,592 --> 00:33:17,432
Alfonso!
Call an ambulance!

307
00:33:18,352 --> 00:33:19,512
Out of the way!

308
00:33:34,872 --> 00:33:37,872
Get up. Let's go.

309
00:33:40,472 --> 00:33:42,432
Come on. Quickly!

310
00:33:43,312 --> 00:33:47,792
Get in before the Border Patrol
finds us!

311
00:33:49,072 --> 00:33:51,192
Watch your head.

312
00:34:11,192 --> 00:34:12,992
Can I speak to Diaz?

313
00:34:13,752 --> 00:34:15,032
What?

314
00:35:01,432 --> 00:35:05,872
He's coming back. Let's go!

315
00:35:42,992 --> 00:35:44,152
What?

316
00:36:16,032 --> 00:36:20,672
- Who did this?
- I don't know. Nobody does.

317
00:36:21,112 --> 00:36:22,912
Diaz is gone.

318
00:36:22,912 --> 00:36:26,552
And tomorrow the bus driver's
gonna be a free man.

319
00:36:26,552 --> 00:36:30,552
No! With Eva's testimony,
he will go to jail.

320
00:36:30,552 --> 00:36:32,952
- Eva's gone.
- What?

321
00:36:32,952 --> 00:36:37,712
She ran away. Nobody knows
where she is, not even her mother.

322
00:36:37,712 --> 00:36:40,872
Her mother. To move away
from Colonia Anapra.

323
00:36:40,872 --> 00:36:45,192
She want to be there for her,
waiting for her at their home...

324
00:36:45,192 --> 00:36:48,632
